    <text>
        <body>
            <head>259. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="recgt3SoCfObWa7Tt">Powell</persName>) to President <persName
                    corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d259fn1">Source: <orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>, National
                    Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR 096, NSDD 295. Secret. Sent for
                    action. Prepared by <persName corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="recASjYJjIDTjOXpN">Tobey</persName>. Copied to <persName
                        corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="recEQQb67MTNPG0x8">Howard Baker</persName>. A stamped notation at
                    the top of the memorandum reads: “<persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">The
                        President</persName> has seen 1/13/88.”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1988-01-12"
                        >January 12, 1988</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Guidance for the Upcoming <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear
                        and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss target="#t_NST_1">NST</gloss>) Negotiating
                    Round</item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>To approve instructions for the ninth round of <rs type="event"
                    corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_NST_1">NST</gloss>) in Geneva.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Background</p>
            <p>The <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> resume
                in Geneva on January 14.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>Draft instructions for the upcoming round have been prepared by the appropriate
                interagency bodies. Normal practice is to document your approval of all instructions
                in an NSDD. A draft NSDD<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d259fn2">Printed as <ref
                        target="#d260">Document 260</ref>.</note> is at <hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">Tab <pb facs="1181" n="1154" xml:id="pg_1154"/>
                A</hi>; it includes as attachments individual instructions for <gloss
                    target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss> and <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> and
                overall <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> instructions.</p>
            <p>In preparing the instructions, several issues arose, none of which I consider to
                require action by you, since none involves new policy. I resolved them as
                follows:</p>
            <p>—Maintained our formal position to ban <rs type="topic" corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID"
                    >mobile</rs>
                <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                </gloss>, based on the desire you expressed during the summit that we make more
                progress in other areas before formally accepting <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recInQ6JTYKBeryID">mobile</rs>
                <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                </gloss>. (<orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> and <gloss
                    target="#t_ACDA_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reckjQkUajOv3dbTz">ACDA</orgName>
                </gloss> opposed)</p>
            <p>—Authorized dropping our past demand for a <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19">sublimit</rs> of 1650 <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> on heavy or highly <gloss
                    target="#t_MIRV_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3jfDwQdQCBVT9H">MIRVd</rs>
                </gloss>
                <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                </gloss>, replacing it with the 1540 <rs type="topic" corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19"
                    >sublimit</rs> on heavy <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                </gloss>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> you agreed to during the
                summit. (<gloss target="#t_OSD_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recoMngX7uLPacWDx">OSD</orgName>
                </gloss>, <gloss target="#t_JCS_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recYt5V8hImTp3Aah">JCS</orgName>
                </gloss> and Ambassador <persName corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName>
                opposed)</p>
            <p>—Accepted wording making it clear that we desire a meaningful constraint on <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missile</rs>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="reclksm3VX3UUxetF">throwweight</rs> in the <gloss
                    target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">treaty</rs> itself.
                    (<orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> and <gloss
                    target="#t_JCS_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recYt5V8hImTp3Aah">JCS</orgName>
                </gloss> opposed)</p>
            <p>—Accepted the <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="reclckIw9AgH05Yxw">INF</rs>
                </gloss> approach to defining <rs type="topic" corresp="recqaxqBsfTYVWHfR">cruise
                    missile</rs> range. (<gloss target="#t_ACDA_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reckjQkUajOv3dbTz">ACDA</orgName>
                </gloss> opposed).</p>
            <p>—Deferred for further study an <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recoMngX7uLPacWDx">OSD</orgName>
                </gloss>/<gloss target="#t_ACDA_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reckjQkUajOv3dbTz">ACDA</orgName>
                </gloss> proposal for additional constraints on the number of <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missile</rs>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> a side could declare a
                missile possesses as well as an <gloss target="#t_ACDA_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reckjQkUajOv3dbTz">ACDA</orgName>
                </gloss>/<orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> proposal to combine
                quotas for various types of inspections.</p>
            <p>—Added new notification requirements for movements of treaty limited items. (<gloss
                    target="#t_JCS_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recYt5V8hImTp3Aah">JCS</orgName>
                </gloss> opposed)</p>
            <p>—Characterized the status of the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs> after the
                period of <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4"
                    >non-withdrawal</rs> in such a way as to protect our right to deploy <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recKKNyP9NHSwF6fs">defenses</rs> after the
                period, without implying a date certain for ending the <rs
                    type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs>.</p>
            <p>In addition, I resolved minor wording issues.</p>
            <p>In accordance with NSDD 266, <persName corresp="recjEGrBBTk23XRP8">Nicholas
                    Rostow</persName>, Legal Adviser to the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName>
                </gloss>, has coordinated the attached NSDD with A.B. Culvahouse in advance of its
                submission to you.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="2">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>That you sign the attached NSDD approving the negotiating instructions for
                            <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                        </gloss> Round IX.<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d259fn3">
                            <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
